Stopping or disabling the IKEEXT service will disable IKE and AuthIP key exchange with peer computers. IPsec is typically configured to use IKE or AuthIP; therefore, stopping or disabling the IKEEXT service might result in an IPsec failure and might compromise the security of the system. It is strongly recommended that you have the IKEEXT service running.

win32_service_multi.caption: IP Helper
win32_service_multi.description: Provides tunnel connectivity using IPv6 transition technologies (6to4, ISATAP, Port Proxy, and Teredo), and IP-HTTPS. If this service is stopped, the computer will not have the enhanced connectivity benefits that these technologies offer.
win32_service_multi.name: iphlpsvc

win32_service_multi.caption: IP Translation Configuration Service
win32_service_multi.description: Configures and enables translation from v4 to v6 and vice versa
win32_service_multi.name: IpxlatCfgSvc

win32_service_multi.caption: IPsec Policy Agent
win32_service_multi.description: Internet Protocol security (IPsec) supports network-level peer authentication, data origin authentication, data integrity, data confidentiality (encryption), and replay protection. This service enforces IPsec policies created through the IP Security Policies snap-in or the command-line tool "netsh ipsec". If you stop this service, you may experience network connectivity issues if your policy requires that connections use IPsec. Also,remote management of Windows Defender Firewall is not available when this service is stopped.
win32_service_multi.name: PolicyAgent

win32_service_multi.caption: KtmRm for Distributed Transaction Coordinator
win32_service_multi.description: Coordinates transactions between the Distributed Transaction Coordinator (MSDTC) and the Kernel Transaction Manager (KTM). If it is not needed, it is recommended that this service remain stopped. If it is needed, both MSDTC and KTM will start this service automatically. If this service is disabled, any MSDTC transaction interacting with a Kernel Resource Manager will fail and any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
win32_service_multi.name: KtmRm

win32_service_multi.caption: Language Experience Service
win32_service_multi.description: Provides infrastructure support for deploying and configuring localized Windows resources. This service is started on demand and, if disabled, additional Windows languages will not be deployed to the system, and Windows may not function properly.
win32_service_multi.name: LxpSvc

win32_service_multi.caption: Link-Layer Topology Discovery Mapper
win32_service_multi.description: Creates a Network Map, consisting of PC and device topology (connectivity) information, and metadata describing each PC and device. If this service is disabled, the Network Map will not function properly.
win32_service_multi.name: lltdsvc

win32_service_multi.caption: Local Profile Assistant Service
win32_service_multi.description: This service provides profile management for subscriber identity modules
win32_service_multi.name: wlpasvc

win32_service_multi.caption: Local Session Manager

win32_service_multi.caption: MessagingService_49269
win32_service_multi.description: Service supporting text messaging and related functionality.

win32_service_multi.caption: Microsoft (R) Diagnostics Hub Standard Collector Service

win32_service_multi.name: diagnosticshub.standardcollector.service

win32_service_multi.caption: Microsoft Account Sign-in Assistant

win32_service_multi.caption: Microsoft App-V Client
win32_service_multi.description: Manages App-V users and virtual applications

win32_service_multi.caption: Microsoft Defender Antivirus Network Inspection Service
win32_service_multi.description: Helps guard against intrusion attempts targeting known and newly discovered vulnerabilities in network protocols

win32_service_multi.name: WdNisSvc

win32_service_multi.caption: Microsoft Defender Antivirus Service

win32_service_multi.name: WinDefend

win32_service_multi.caption: Microsoft Edge Elevation Service (MicrosoftEdgeElevationService)
win32_service_multi.description: Keeps Microsoft Edge up to update. If this service is disabled, the application will not be kept up to date.
win32_service_multi.name: MicrosoftEdgeElevationService

win32_service_multi.caption: Microsoft iSCSI Initiator Service
win32_service_multi.description: Manages Internet SCSI (iSCSI) sessions from this computer to remote iSCSI target devices. If this service is stopped, this computer will not be able to login or access iSCSI targets. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
win32_service_multi.name: MSiSCSI

win32_service_multi.caption: Microsoft Passport
win32_service_multi.description: Provides process isolation for cryptographic keys used to provide authentication to a users associated identity providers. If this service is disabled, all uses and management of these keys will not be available, which includes machine log-on and single sign-on for apps and websites. This service starts and stops automatically. It is recommended that you do not reconfigure this service.
win32_service_multi.name: NgcSvc

win32_service_multi.caption: Microsoft Passport Container
win32_service_multi.description: Manages local user identity keys used to authenticate the user to identity providers, as well as TPM virtual smart cards. win32_service_multi.name: NgcCtnrSvc

win32_service_multi.caption: Microsoft Software Shadow Copy Provider
win32_service_multi.description: Manages software-based volume shadow copies taken by the Volume Shadow Copy service. If this service is stopped, software-based volume shadow copies cannot be managed. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
win32_service_multi.name: swprv

win32_service_multi.caption: Microsoft Storage Spaces SMP
win32_service_multi.description: Host service for the Microsoft Storage Spaces management provider. If this service is stopped or disabled, Storage Spaces cannot be managed.
win32_service_multi.name: smphost

win32_service_multi.caption: Microsoft Store Install Service
win32_service_multi.description: Provides infrastructure support for the Microsoft Store. This service is started on demand, and if disabled then installations will not function properly.

win32_service_multi.caption: Microsoft Windows SMS Router Service.
win32_service_multi.description: Routes messages based on rules to appropriate clients.

win32_service_multi.caption: Natural Authentication

win32_service_multi.caption: Net.Tcp Port Sharing Service

win32_service_multi.caption: Netlogon
win32_service_multi.description: Maintains a secure channel between this computer and the domain controller for authenticating users and services. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
win32_service_multi.name: Netlogon

win32_service_multi.caption: Network Connected Devices Auto-Setup
win32_service_multi.description: Network Connected Devices Auto-Setup service monitors and installs qualified devices that connect to a qualified network. Users can still manually add network connected devices to a PC through the user interface.

win32_service_multi.caption: Network Connection Broker
win32_service_multi.description: Brokers connections that allow Windows Store Apps to receive notifications from the internet.
win32_service_multi.name: NcbService

win32_service_multi.caption: Network Connections
win32_service_multi.description: Manages objects in the Network and Dial-Up Connections folder, in which you can view both local area network and remote connections.

win32_service_multi.caption: Network Connectivity Assistant
win32_service_multi.description: Provides DirectAccess status notification for UI components
win32_service_multi.name: NcaSvc

win32_service_multi.caption: Network List Service

win32_service_multi.caption: Network Location Awareness

win32_service_multi.name: NlaSvc

win32_service_multi.caption: Network Setup Service

win32_service_multi.caption: Network Store Interface Service

win32_service_multi.caption: Offline Files

win32_service_multi.caption: OpenSSH Authentication Agent

win32_service_multi.caption: Payments and NFC/SE Manager

win32_service_multi.name: p2pimsvc

win32_service_multi.caption: Performance Counter DLL Host
win32_service_multi.description: Enables remote users and 64-bit processes to query performance counters provided by 32-bit DLLs. If this service is stopped, only local users and 32-bit processes will be able to query performance counters provided by 32-bit DLLs.

win32_service_multi.caption: Performance Logs & Alerts
win32_service_multi.description: Performance Logs and Alerts Collects performance data from local or remote computers based on preconfigured schedule parameters, then writes the data to a log or triggers an alert. If this service is stopped, performance information will not be collected. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
win32_service_multi.name: pla

win32_service_multi.caption: Phone Service
win32_service_multi.description: Manages the telephony state on the device
win32_service_multi.name: PhoneSvc

win32_service_multi.caption: Plug and Play
win32_service_multi.description: Enables a computer to recognize and adapt to hardware changes with little or no user input. Stopping or disabling this service will result in system instability.

win32_service_multi.caption: PNRP Machine Name Publication Service

win32_service_multi.description: This service opens custom printer dialogue boxes and handles notifications from a remote print server or a printer. If you turn this service off, you wont be able to see printer extensions or notifications.
win32_service_multi.name: PrintNotify

win32_service_multi.caption: PrintWorkflow_49269
win32_service_multi.description: Provides support for Print Workflow applications. If you turn off this service, you may not be able to print successfully.
win32_service_multi.name: PrintWorkflowUserSvc_49269

win32_service_multi.caption: Problem Reports Control Panel Support
win32_service_multi.description: This service provides support for viewing, sending and deletion of system-level problem reports for the Problem Reports control panel.

win32_service_multi.caption: Program Compatibility Assistant Service
win32_service_multi.description: This service provides support for the Program Compatibility Assistant (PCA). PCA monitors programs installed and run by the user and detects known compatibility problems. If this service is stopped, PCA will not function properly.

win32_service_multi.caption: Recommended Troubleshooting Service
win32_service_multi.description: Enables automatic mitigation for known problems by applying recommended troubleshooting. If stopped, your device will not get recommended troubleshooting for problems on your device.
win32_service_multi.name: TroubleshootingSvc

win32_service_multi.caption: Remote Access Auto Connection Manager
win32_service_multi.description: Creates a connection to a remote network whenever a program references a remote DNS or NetBIOS name or address.
win32_service_multi.name: RasAuto

win32_service_multi.caption: Remote Access Connection Manager
win32_service_multi.description: Manages dial-up and virtual private network (VPN) connections from this computer to the Internet or other remote networks. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
win32_service_multi.name: RasMan

win32_service_multi.caption: Remote Desktop Configuration
win32_service_multi.description: Remote Desktop Configuration service (RDCS) is responsible for all Remote Desktop Services and Remote Desktop related configuration and session maintenance activities that require SYSTEM context. These include per-session temporary folders, RD themes, and RD certificates.
win32_service_multi.name: SessionEnv

win32_service_multi.caption: Remote Desktop Services
win32_service_multi.description: Allows users to connect interactively to a remote computer. Remote Desktop and Remote Desktop Session Host Server depend on this service. To prevent remote use of this computer, clear the checkboxes on the Remote tab of the System properties control panel item.
win32_service_multi.name: TermService

win32_service_multi.caption: Remote Desktop Services UserMode Port Redirector
win32_service_multi.description: Allows the redirection of Printers/Drives/Ports for RDP connections
win32_service_multi.displayname: Remote Desktop Services UserMode Port Redirector
win32_service_multi.name: UmRdpService

win32_service_multi.caption: Remote Procedure Call (RPC)
win32_service_multi.description: The RPCSS service is the Service Control Manager for COM and DCOM servers. It performs object activations requests, object exporter resolutions and distributed garbage collection for COM and DCOM servers. If this service is stopped or disabled, programs using COM or DCOM will not function properly. It is strongly recommended that you have the RPCSS service running.
win32_service_multi.name: RpcSs

win32_service_multi.caption: Remote Procedure Call (RPC) Locator
win32_service_multi.description: In Windows 2003 and earlier versions of Windows, the Remote Procedure Call (RPC) Locator service manages the RPC name service database. In Windows Vista and later versions of Windows, this service does not provide any functionality and is present for application compatibility.
win32_service_multi.name: RpcLocator

win32_service_multi.caption: Remote Registry
win32_service_multi.description: Enables remote users to modify registry settings on this computer. If this service is stopped, the registry can be modified only by users on this computer. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
win32_service_multi.name: RemoteRegistry

win32_service_multi.caption: Retail Demo Service
win32_service_multi.description: The Retail Demo service controls device activity while the device is in retail demo mode.
win32_service_multi.name: RetailDemo

win32_service_multi.caption: Routing and Remote Access
win32_service_multi.description: Offers routing services to businesses in local area and wide area network environments.
win32_service_multi.name: RemoteAccess

win32_service_multi.caption: RPC Endpoint Mapper
win32_service_multi.description: Resolves RPC interfaces identifiers to transport endpoints. If this service is stopped or disabled, programs using Remote Procedure Call (RPC) services will not function properly.
win32_service_multi.name: RpcEptMapper

win32_service_multi.caption: Secondary Log-on
win32_service_multi.description: Enables starting processes under alternate credentials. If this service is stopped, this type of log-on access will be unavailable. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
win32_service_multi.name: seclogon

win32_service_multi.caption: Secure Socket Tunneling Protocol Service
win32_service_multi.description: Provides support for the Secure Socket Tunneling Protocol (SSTP) to connect to remote computers using VPN. If this service is disabled, users will not be able to use SSTP to access remote servers.
win32_service_multi.name: SstpSvc

win32_service_multi.caption: Security Accounts Manager
win32_service_multi.description: The startup of this service signals other services that the Security Accounts Manager (SAM) is ready to accept requests. Disabling this service will prevent other services in the system from being notified when the SAM is ready, which may in turn cause those services to fail to start correctly. This service should not be disabled.
win32_service_multi.name: SamSs

win32_service_multi.caption: Security Center
win32_service_multi.description: The WSCSVC (Windows Security Center) service monitors and reports security health settings on the computer. The health settings include firewall (on/off), antivirus (on/off/out of date), antispyware (on/off/out of date), Windows Update (automatically/manually download and install updates), User Account Control (on/off), and Internet settings (recommended/not recommended). The service provides COM APIs for independent software vendors to register and record the state of their products to the Security Center service. The Security and Maintenance UI uses the service to provide systray alerts and a graphical view of the security health states in the Security and Maintenance control panel. Network Access Protection (NAP) uses the service to report the security health states of clients to the NAP Network Policy Server to make network quarantine decisions. The service also has a public API that allows external consumers to programmatically retrieve the aggregated security health state of the system.
win32_service_multi.name: wscsvc

win32_service_multi.caption: Sensor Data Service
win32_service_multi.description: Delivers data from a variety of sensors
win32_service_multi.name: SensorDataService

win32_service_multi.description: Monitors various sensors in order to expose data and adapt to system and user state. If this service is stopped or disabled, the display brightness will not adapt to lighting conditions. Stopping this service may affect other system functionality and features as well.
win32_service_multi.name: SensrSvc

win32_service_multi.caption: Sensor Service
win32_service_multi.description: A service for sensors that manages different sensors' functionality. Manages Simple Device Orientation (SDO) and History for sensors. Loads the SDO sensor that reports device orientation changes. If this service is stopped or disabled, the SDO sensor will not be loaded and so auto-rotation will not occur. History collection from Sensors will also be stopped.
win32_service_multi.name: SensorService

win32_service_multi.caption: Server
win32_service_multi.description: Supports file, print, and named-pipe sharing over the network for this computer. If this service is stopped, these functions will be unavailable. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
win32_service_multi.name: LanmanServer

win32_service_multi.caption: Shared PC Account Manager
win32_service_multi.description: Manages profiles and accounts on a SharedPC configured device
win32_service_multi.name: shpamsvc

win32_service_multi.caption: Shell Hardware Detection
win32_service_multi.description: Provides notifications for AutoPlay hardware events.
win32_service_multi.name: ShellHWDetection

win32_service_multi.caption: Smart Card
win32_service_multi.description: Manages access to smart cards read by this computer. If this service is stopped, this computer will be unable to read smart cards. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
win32_service_multi.name: SCardSvr

win32_service_multi.caption: Smart Card Device Enumeration Service
win32_service_multi.description: Creates software device nodes for all smart card readers accessible to a given session. If this service is disabled, WinRT APIs will not be able to enumerate smart card readers.

win32_service_multi.caption: Smart Card Removal Policy
win32_service_multi.description: Allows the system to be configured to lock the user desktop upon smart card removal.

win32_service_multi.caption: Software Protection
win32_service_multi.description: Enables the download, installation and enforcement of digital licenses for Windows and Windows applications. win32_service_multi.caption: State Repository Service
win32_service_multi.description: Provides required infrastructure support for the application model.

win32_service_multi.caption: Still Image Acquisition Events

win32_service_multi.name: StorSvc

win32_service_multi.caption: Storage Tiers Management
win32_service_multi.description: Optimizes the placement of data in storage tiers on all tiered storage spaces in the system.
